commText: Head and Abhishek Sharma are at the crease. Head is on strike. N Thushara will open the attack
N Thushara to Head, 2 wides, inswinger that finishes well down leg, Head doesn't get bat on it and Kishan does well to get a hand diving across to his right

N Thushara to Abhishek Sharma, no run, another inswinger, again down the leg-side, but this time the umpire doesn't call it wide. Abhishek immediately asks for it to be reviewed. It looks very close to pad on the replay, and UltraEdge confirms it has touched the pad. Review wasted!

N Thushara to Abhishek Sharma, no run, wow there's another review for a wide, this time from MI! Full toss outside off, Abhishek advances and decides to let it go. It's clearly inside the marker, so the decision will be overturned
N Thushara to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 135kph length ball on off, inswinger, Abhishek looks to defend and gets a thick inside edge behind square
N Thushara to Head, no run, back of a length delivery on leg stump, inswinger, Head hangs back and gently bunts it to mid-on
Already the bounce has been low on this pitch. Looks on the slower side as well
N Thushara to Head, no run, 138kph length ball outside off, Head goes hard at it but he's through the shot early because of the slowness of the surface. He drags it off the inside half to midwicket
N Thushara to Head, FOUR, inside edge runs away to the boundary! Slower ball floated up on off, Head has a big swing, goes through the shot early and drags it past leg stump
Anshul Kamboj, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Anshul Kamboj to Abhishek Sharma, wide, short and wide, Abhishek goes after it but fails to reach out
Anshul Kamboj to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 136kph back of a length delivery on off, angling away from the left-hander, Abhishek opens the face and steers it to the left of short third

Anshul Kamboj to Head, 1 run, 135.7kph good length ball across off, Head stays back and looks to slap it hard through the off-side. He mistimes it to the left of cover and gets across for a quick single
Anshul Kamboj to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 139kph back of a length delivery across off, Abhishek wafts at it loosely and is beaten on the edge
Anshul Kamboj to Abhishek Sharma, SIX, back of a length outside off, enough width for Abhishek to free the arms and he slaps it hard over extra cover. Goes for a 78-meter six!
Anshul Kamboj to Abhishek Sharma, leg byes, 1 run, 137.5kph back of a length delivery down leg, Abhishek looks to clip it away but it goes off his thigh pad to fine leg
Anshul Kamboj to Head, FOUR, again a boundary off the inside edge for Head! Looks to cut a ball that's not wide enough, and nearly chops it onto the stumps
N Thushara to Abhishek Sharma, leg byes, 1 run, full ball swinging in, Abhishek looks to whip it away but is hit on the pad. Would've easily missed leg stump

N Thushara to Head, no run, lovely inswinger that goes right through Head and almost takes out leg stump! He's riding his luck out there. Fuller than a length, cramps Head for room as he looks to loft down the ground and goes past the inside edge
N Thushara to Head, 1 run, full on middle, Head hammers it down the ground but MI have a long-on in place
N Thushara to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 139kph full inswinger around middle, Abhishek looks to whip it away but gets an inside edge onto pad
N Thushara to Head, FOUR, slower ball floated up on off, Head clears the front leg and looks to smack it down the ground. Doesn't quite get hold of it but has enough to send it racing past mid-off
N Thushara to Head, no run, slower bouncer outside off, deceives Head completely as he goes through the pull too early. Beaten!
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Bumrah starts from round the wicket
Bumrah to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, back of a length on off, nipping back in, Abhishek stays in the crease and tucks it behind square
Bumrah to Head, 1 run, 140.5kph inswinging yorker just outside off, Head looks to squeeze it away and gets another inside edge past leg stump
Bumrah to Abhishek Sharma, 1 run, 138.9kph back of a length delivery on off, Abhishek hangs back and tucks it wide of mid-on
Bumrah to Head, 1 run, now an away-swinging yorker on off stump, Head picks it and squeezes it to mid-off
Bumrah to Abhishek Sharma, no run, pitched right up just outside off, 129.8kph, Abhishek looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto back pad
Bumrah to Abhishek Sharma, no run, 142.2kph back of a length delivery on off, nips back in and strikes Abhishek on the thigh as he looks to tuck it through the on-side
Shot-making not easy at all on this slow surface so far and both these openers have struggled. Head, in particular, has been riding his luck
Anshul Kamboj [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Anshul Kamboj to Head, no run, fuller than a length on off, Head clears the front leg and hammers it to mid-off

Anshul Kamboj to Head, SIX, back of a length delivery on leg stump, sits up around the waist and Head dispatches it with a cracking pull shot. Didn't have room to extend his arms properly, but the timing is brilliant. Goes all the way over midwicket
Kamboj goes round the wicket
Anshul Kamboj to Head, no run, back of a length delivery around off, Head makes room looking to slap it over the off-side but misses
Anshul Kamboj to Head, 2 runs, backs away again, gets a delivery following him and somehow pulls it through midwicket. David cuts it off in the deep

Anshul Kamboj to Head, no ball, off stump out of the ground, but it's a no-ball! Oh dear! Would've been the first IPL wicket for Kamboj, but instead he has to now deal with a free hit next ball. Fuller than a length delivery slanted in, Head makes room to swing but it straightens past the edge and crashes into off stump. However, Kamboj has overstepped
Anshul Kamboj to Head, no ball, FOUR, full ball in the slot, Head clears the front leg and launches it over midwicket. Another no-ball from Kamboj. It's falling apart for him very quickly
Anshul Kamboj to Head, FOUR, goes for a yorker, misses by a long margin and again offers it in the slot. Head comfortably lofts it over the fielder at mid-on for four more
Anshul Kamboj to Head, 1 run, fuller than a length on off, Head looks to slog and drags it off a thick inside edge behind square

Over summary (1-5) -> Debutant Kamboj goes for 14 runs in his first over -> Thushara troubles Head on a few occasions -> Bumrah bowls an excellent over, concedes only 4 runs -> Head gets clean bowled by Kamboj but off a no ball -> 50 up for Sunrisers Hyderabad in the 5th over

Bumrah to Head, FOUR, sloppy work on the field! Frustration grows for MI as another one races to the boundary. Length ball on off, Head hangs back, opens the face and steers to the right of short third. Should've been stopped by Thushara but he lets it through. Tilak goes up to him and tries to cheer him up
Bumrah to Head, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, Head tucks it to deep square leg
Bumrah to Abhishek Sharma, no run, back of a length on off, Abhishek hangs back and steers it to backward point
Bumrah to Abhishek Sharma, no run, full toss outside off, Abhishek steers it wide of point who makes a diving stop
Bumrah to Abhishek Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! Bumrah raises his arms in quiet celebration as MI get the breakthrough! Length ball outside off from round the wicket, Abhishek pokes at it without moving his feet and edges it to the keeper. Wanted to steer it through it through the off-side but the ball straightened a touch. Good diving catch to his left by Kishan. Abhishek Sharma c Ishan Kishan b Bumrah 11(16) [6s-1]
Mayank Agarwal, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Mayank, no run, pitched right up around off, Agarwal looks to drive and drags it off the inside half to midwicket

Timeout! It was a struggle for both SRH openers in the powerplay, but the scoreboard is what matters and it shows Head currently not out on 38 off 21. He has ridden his luck out there. Inside-edges past the stumps, mistimes shots, bowled off a no-ball. SRH will take it.
Hardik Pandya, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Head, FOUR, back of a length on middle, Head hops back in the crease and whips it over midwicket. Brilliant shot for four!
Hardik Pandya to Head, 1 run, cuts this away to sweeper cover
Hardik Pandya to Mayank, 1 run, back of a length on middle and leg, slower one, Agarwal tucks it behind square
Hardik Pandya to Head, 1 run, length ball on off, Head drives hard down the ground to long-on
Hardik Pandya to Mayank, no run, 132.6kph length ball on off stump, Agarwal hangs back and defends

Hardik Pandya to Mayank, FOUR, crunched off the front foot! Fuller than a length outside off, Agarwal gets forward and plays a lovely drive through extra cover. It races away to the boundary in no time
Kamboj from over the wicket
Anshul Kamboj [2.0-0-32-0] is back into the attack
Anshul Kamboj to Head, no run, 134.9kph length ball on middle, Head hangs back and defends

Anshul Kamboj to Head, 1 run, dropped! Thushara puts down a simple catch and Head gets another life. Full delivery around off, he looks to slog and it flies off a thick edge to deep third. He goes with the reverse-cup but doesn't hold on
Anshul Kamboj to Mayank, no run, looks to tuck it away but is hit on the thigh
Anshul Kamboj to Mayank, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Anshul Kamboj to Mayank, out Bowled!! Kamboj hits the stumps again and this time it's a legal delivery. First IPL wicket for the 23-year old after what's been a very eventful start to his career. Length ball around off, Agarwal makes room to slap it through the off-side but misses. It knocks over the off-bail and Kamboj explodes in celebration. Mayank b Anshul Kamboj 5(6) [4s-1]
Nitish Reddy, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Anshul Kamboj to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, full delivery around off, Reddy turns it through midwicket and gets back for two
Anshul Kamboj to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, length ball on middle and leg, Reddy hangs back and works it through square leg
Hardik Pandya to Nitish Reddy, no run, good length outside off, Reddy pokes at it but it nips away past the edge
Hardik Pandya to Nitish Reddy, FOUR, again a bit of seam movement away from the batter. Fuller than a length around off, Reddy looks to defend but it runs away off a thick edge past the keeper
Hardik Pandya to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, back of a length on off, Reddy dabs it to deep third
Round the wicket to Head
Hardik Pandya to Head, 1 run, back of a length delivery on leg, Head tucks it through midwicket
Hardik Pandya to Nitish Reddy, FOUR, superb shot! Back of a length on off, Reddy hops in the crease, gets on top of it and punches very sweetly through backward point
Hardik Pandya to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, length ball outside off, Reddy shuffles across and steers it to deep third
Mayank Agarwal in IPL 2024 32 (21) vs KKR 11 (13) vs MI 16 (17) vs GT 5 (6) vs MI*
Anshul Kamboj to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, fuller than a length on off, Reddy shuffles across and flicks it behind square. He charges back for two and makes it in time
Anshul Kamboj to Nitish Reddy, no run, pitched up just outside off, Reddy looks to drive but it nips away past the edge
Anshul Kamboj to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, 135.6kph back of a length delivery on off, nips in a touch and takes a thick inside edge into the square leg region
Anshul Kamboj to Head, 1 run, good length on off, Head hangs back and punches to sweeper cover
There's evidence of dew on the outfield
Anshul Kamboj to Nitish Reddy, no run, back of a length on off, Reddy takes a step down the pitch and has to deal with the ball cutting away late. He adjusts and defends

Anshul Kamboj to Nitish Reddy, 2 runs, miscued in the air, and lands just wide of mid-off! Length ball on middle, Reddy makes room to hoist it over the infield on the off-side but doesn't get hold of it at all. Gets away with it
Over summary (6-10) -> Bumrah breaks the opening stand, Abhishek is caught behind -> Thushara puts down Head's catch at third man -> Kamboj finally gets his maiden wicket, Agarwal is bowled
Piyush Chawla, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chawla to Head, 1 run, length ball on middle, googly, Head goes back and punches to long-off
Chawla to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, flat on off, back of a length, Reddy stays back and whips it to long-on
MI spinners have taken just 10 wickets - least among all the teams this season.
Chawla to Head, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chawla to Head, out Caught by Tilak Varma!! Head's luck runs out as Chawla strikes in his first over. Tossed up on leg stump, Head goes on one knee for the sweep but hits it straight to deep backward square. Simple catch for Tilak who makes no mistake. Head c Tilak Varma b Chawla 48(30) [4s-7 6s-1]
Slip in place for Klaasen
Heinrich Klaasen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chawla to Klaasen, no run, oh the googly almost sneaks right through him! Length ball on off, Klaasen hangs back to defend and gets a thick inside edge into the pitch

Chawla to Klaasen, 1 run, goes for a lofted shot but doesn't get hold of it. Full ball on off, Klaasen looks to hit straight, doesn't get it off the middle and it goes in the air. The ball falls safely to the right of David at long-off and he does well to cut off the boundary
Chawla to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, clipped down to long-on
Hardik Pandya [2.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Nitish Reddy, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Hardik Pandya to Nitish Reddy, out Caught by Anshul Kamboj!! Wickets in successive overs for MI as Reddy perishes as well. Short of length outside off, he looks to pull but is beaten for pace, getting it very high on the bat. It balloons in the air and Kamboj takes it at point. More evidence of the two-paced nature of this track. Nitish Reddy c Anshul Kamboj b Hardik Pandya 20(15) [4s-2]
Marco Jansen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Hardik Pandya to Marco Jansen, no run, fuller than a length outside off, Jansen looks to drive but it nips away past the edge

Travis Head vs spin in IPL 2024 Inns: 8 Runs: 90 Balls: 62 Dismissals: 5 Avg: 18.0 SR: 145.2
Hardik Pandya to Marco Jansen, 1 run, length ball outside off, Jansen gets forward and steers it wide of backward point
Hardik Pandya to Klaasen, 1 run, fuller than a length just outside off, Klaasen knocks it through the point region
Hardik Pandya to Marco Jansen, no run, banged in short outside off, Jansen looks to pull but is beaten

Hardik Pandya to Marco Jansen, 2 runs, Jansen is early through the drive and it goes in the air. But he finds the gap at extra cover. Fuller than a length just outside off, the ball stops on him perhaps and he's not in control. Goes right in the gap though. The mid-off fielder does a superb job in hunting it down
Chawla to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Chawla to Klaasen, out Bowled!! Big slog from Klaasen and he drags it onto the stumps off the inside edge! MI are pumped. A whole bunch of inside edges evaded the stumps from Head earlier, but Klaasen has no such luck. He looks to take down Chawla as he tosses one up around off, plays across the line and chops on. SRH have now lost five for 40. Klaasen b Chawla 2(4)
Shahbaz Ahmed, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Heinrich Klaasen vs Piyush Chawla in IPL Inns: 4 Runs: 29 Balls: 17 Dismissals: 2
Chawla to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, length ball on middle, Shahbaz shuffles across and works it through square leg
Chawla to Marco Jansen, 1 run, tossed up on off, Jansen flicks to long-on
Chawla to Shahbaz Ahmed, 2 runs, length ball outside off, Shahbaz goes back, uses the pace and dabs it past slip. Backward point chases it down
Chawla to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, googly outside off, Shahbaz looks to cut but is beaten. Reckon Chawla is a bit lucky to get away with a wide
Chawla to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, length ball on off, Shahbaz goes back and punches to long-on

Over summary (11-13) -> Chawla removes Head, he is caught at deep square leg -> Pandya gets Nitish Reddy, MI making a comeback -> Chawla strikes again, Klaasen is bowled off an inside edge -> 100 up for Sunrisers in the 13th over
Jasprit Bumrah [2.0-0-9-1] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Shahbaz Ahmed, 2 runs, good length delivery just outside off, Shahbaz Ahmed hangs back and eases it down to third man for a couple
Bumrah to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, pitched up full and just outside off, driven nicely but straight to the man at cover
Bumrah to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, full on off-stump, Shahbaz Ahmed bunts it towards point for a quick single
Bumrah to Marco Jansen, wide, banged in short and going down leg, that will be a wide
MI review. This is for the wide that was given the previous delivery, terrible review, they've thrown one away here
Bumrah to Marco Jansen, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, tucked into the leg-side towards mid-wicket for one
Bumrah to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, banged in short and going down leg, Shahbaz Ahmed looked to heave it away and missed, not called a wide this time
Bumrah to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, very full and just outside off, punched towards mid-on for one
Chawla to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, length delivery on off-stump, Shahbaz Ahmed presses back and works it towards mid-wicket for one
Chawla to Marco Jansen, 1 run, wrong-un full on off-stump, worked away to deep mid-wicket
Chawla to Shahbaz Ahmed, 1 run, tossed up full and on the pads, swept away to deep backward square leg, just one
Chawla to Marco Jansen, no run, length delivery just outside off, Marco Jansen leant in looking to paddle and was struck on the pad
Chawla to Marco Jansen, SIX, he's sent that into the crowd! Floated up full on off-stump, was the wrong-un and Marco Jansen picked it, he pressed forward and slogged it over cow corner for a maximum
Chawla to Marco Jansen, FOUR, nicely done! Full on off-stump, Marco Jansen leant across and just used the pace to paddle that very fine, man at long leg couldn't get around

Timeout. MI have done brilliantly in this middle phase. They've got SRH by the scruff of their neck and now they've got to be careful not to release that grip and let SRH get away with some quick runs. SRH need this pair to carry on a bit longer, they've still got Samad and Cummins in the shed though
Hardik Pandya [3.0-0-26-1] is back into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Shahbaz Ahmed, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Hardik Pandya to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Caught by Suryakumar Yadav!! Skipper gets the breakthrough! Full and straight on middle, Shahbaz Ahmed looked to pick it up and loft it over long-on but it came right out of the toe end, went high in the air and SKY covered good ground as he run in from long-on towards the circle, judged it nicely and took a sliding catch. Another wicket at just the right time for MI. Shahbaz Ahmed c Suryakumar Yadav b Hardik Pandya 10(12)
Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Hardik Pandya to Abdul Samad, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Abdul Samad presses back and eases it out towards deep point
Hardik Pandya to Marco Jansen, 1 run, length delivery outside off, Marco Jansen stands tall and slaps it aerially towards sweeper cover, doesn't get it into the gap
Hardik Pandya to Abdul Samad, 1 run, back of a length on off-stump, Abdul Samad just tucks it round the corner to long leg for one
Hardik Pandya to Marco Jansen, wide, full and wide outside off, was just on the line there, oh dear they burn a review
Hardik Pandya to Marco Jansen, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Hardik Pandya to Marco Jansen, out Bowled!! Straight through him! Hardik's got his third wicket for the night! A good length delivery on middle, nipped back in very sharply and skidded through, Marco Jansen was looking to pull that but was caught in no man's land with his footwork, it rushed him and thudded into leg-stump. Jansen has to go and SRH are 7 down. Marco Jansen b Hardik Pandya 17(12) [4s-1 6s-1]

Hardik Pandya to Cummins, 1 run, pushed to mid-on for a single
Chawla to Cummins, wide, flatter delivery that just slides down leg, was a wrong-un

Chawla to Cummins, SIX, Cummins gets hold of one! Full outside off, was in the slot and Cummins smacked it over long-on with a clean swing of the blade, he's more than handy with the bat
Chawla to Cummins, 1 run, full on middle, worked away towards square leg
Chawla to Abdul Samad, 1 run, full on middle-leg, Samad leans in and has a big swipe, ends up mistiming it down to deep mid-wicket
Chawla to Cummins, 1 run, full on middle, worked away to square leg
Chawla to Abdul Samad, wide, length delivery wide outside off, too wide
SRH review. Samad has been given out lbw
Chawla to Abdul Samad, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Chawla to Abdul Samad, out Lbw!! Chawla gets a third wicket as well! The review seemed to be a mere formality because the batter had already walked to the boundary ropes after having one look at the replay. Was a length delivery on off-stump and a wrong-un, Abdul Samad hung back looking to work it into the leg-side and played all around, was struck pretty straight in front and the umpire had no hesitation in raising the finger. Nothing on UltraEdge and Hawkeye returned with 3 reds. Abdul Samad lbw b Chawla 3(4)

Bumrah to Sanvir Singh, 1 run, slower delivery full and wide outside off, knocked out towards deep cover

Bumrah to Cummins, no run, nails the yorker! Just just outside off and it snuck under the toe end as Cummins looked to dig it out, that was mighty close to off-stump

N Thushara to Cummins, wide, length delivery very wide outside off, saw Cummins shuffling across and pushed it even wider

N Thushara to Sanvir Singh, 1 run, full and wide outside off, sliced out towards backward point for a quick single

N Thushara to Cummins, SIX, that's been clubbed! Length delivery just outside off, Cummins stood still and pumped it over long-off, just about got enough to clear the man there and the ropes

N Thushara to Cummins, 2 runs, length delivery wide outside off, Cummins reaches out and drags it down the ground, no timing and the man at long-on gets around, two more taken

21:24 Local Time, 15:54 GMT, 21:24 IST: A pretty decent recovery from SRH here to post 173. It might not be amongst the obnoxiously high totals we've gotten used to but this surface isn't a highway either. After being asked to bat first, SRH started well enough in the powerplay. The opening partnership was worth 56 and while Abhishek Sharma struggled tonight, Travis Head carted them around after getting a couple of reprieves - first getting bowled off a no-ball and then getting dropped. But it was after the powerplay that the trouble started for SRH. Mumbai bowled really well through the middle overs and kept picking up wickets at regular intervals. Both Hardik and Piyush Chawla were instrumental in that stage and both ended up with 3 wickets each. SRH were 125/7 at the end of the 16th over but a lovely cameo from Cummins (35* off 17) meant that MI weren't quite able to contain the opposition to a cheap total. The wicket seemed to be slightly two-paced and it held up on occasions so if SRH bowl well, they're definitely in with a chance. Back shortly.

Chawla: It's not gripping that much because a lot of dew has already come in. For seamers there's quite a bit of help. This season, batters go for it if they see the ball a little pitched up even if they are new to the crease - I didn't realise that in the first few matches, but got the idea later about what length to bowl. 173 isn't going to be that easy, we'll still have to bat well. No, there's hardly anything for spinners in this wicket.

Out come the players. There's already a lot of dew and that might be a factor that aids the MI batters just a bit here. Still, it's important for these two to see off the new ball, there will be some swing on offer early on. Right, slip in place to start
